race.comment: GRAND EAGLE (2) looks to get a much better set-up back in this class with a fast tempo assured. Buried back in the field and got out when the race was all over to finish fifth over this trip at Rosehill in the G2 Roman Consul. Rawiller sticks and will prove hard to hold out. MISS FREELOVE (8) slow into stride at her second run back before circling the field for a dominant win in fast time over 1100m at Warwick Farm. Looks ready for this and shapes as the main danger. MEMO (1) Group 3 winning filly who was stiff not to win at her second run back when getting out late to run second in the G3 Scarborough Stakes over 1200m at Moonee Valley. Kept up to the mark with a recent 1030m trial placing and gets her chance. YOUNG MISTER GRACE (5) undefeated Anders colt who smashed the clock when making it two straight wins over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Likely leader who will give a ton of cheek. PALLATON (3) frustrating colt who drops a few levels fourth-up. Will go back from the draw and need luck.
